title: For Sale:  Colt Model 357 for Sale
postcontent: For sale is a 1959 Colt Model 3-5-7 with 4" barrel and target hammer. This fine handgun was the precursor of the legendary Python and was Colt's premium handgun in the 1950's. In fact with the exception of the shrouded barrel, the two guns are identical. This example is in excellent condition both in appearance and mechanical function with just the slightest hint of wear on the very end of the muzzle. The hand-fitted lockwork is as tight as a new gun and the rifling is bright and crisp. These guns are capable of shooting the powerful .357 as well as .38 special rounds. The stocks in the picture are reproductions of the Colt full-checkered design. Included with the gun are its original Colt service style grips that are in excellent condition as well. I do not have an original box. The gun comes in a soft case. The value of this model Colt has risen rapidly in recent years and examples in this condition are getting harder to find. This is as fine a shooting revolver as has ever been made.

title: For Sale:  Colt DA 38 New Army/Navy 1899
postcontent: Here for sell or trade is a Colt DA 38 New Army. Majority of bluing is gone, very minor pitting is visible on the sideplate. The gun has two broken springs, but can still be fired. One broken spring allows the cylender to be rotaded counter clockwise when the hammer is down. This is not a huge issue and the original DA 38s didnt even have this part. The other more important spring is on the hand. I have found that the gun typically still functions, as long as you dont aim up. I have done some shooting with it, no major issues other than the occasional failure for the hand to return. This gun certainly aint for self defense, but I'd make a decent shooter or collector. It's chambered for 38 Long Colt, which can be loaded for using standard 38spl brass. I'll even throw in my remaining Black Powder loaded cartridges with the gun. The grips aren't original, and If you want new grips I have discovered that the gun fits Colt I frame grips. The gun is an antique, no need for a chl or ppp, but I will ask to see your driver's license just in case.I'm open for cash or trade offers, all offers will e accepted.
